value.value: The treatment involving an exposure of reference/experimental plant to monocot plant genus Cyperus found in its growth environment. This plant may be growing as a weed or as part of normal farming practices.
The treatment involving an exposure of plant to the pest Scirpophaga spp.
A bacterial plant exposure (PECO:0007246) involving the exposure to bacteria of the genus Erwinia.
A bacterial plant exposure (PECO:0007246) involving the exposure to bacteria of the genus Pseudomonas.
A bacterial plant exposure (PECO:0007246) involving the exposure to bacteria of the genus Xanthomonas.
The treatment involving use of gravity factor to study various types of responses in presence, absence or modified levels of gravity.
An abiotic plant exposure (PECO:0007191) involving the use of a solid or liquid substrate for growing plants or tissue-cultured plant samples.
The treatment involving an exposure of plant to the pathogen Xanthomonas oryzae. It is a causal agent for rice bacterial blight disease.
A chemical exposure (PECO:0007189) involving use of mutagen for the mutagenesis process.
A physical plant exposure (PECO:0007316) involving an exposure with a radiation type, intensity or quantity.

definition.value: Electromagnetic radiation is classified according to the frequency of its waves. The electromagnetic spectrum, in order of increasing frequency and decreasing wavelength, consists of radio waves, microwaves, infrared radiation, visible light, ultraviolet radiation, X-rays and gamma rays.

value.value: The treatment involving amount of energy of any radiation incident upon (or flowing through) unit area, perpendicular to the radiation source, in unit time.

In biological experiments it refer to the treatment involving radiation in terms of length of the exposure time. It also includes the quantity of radiation falling on a per unit area. This is expressed in the units of luminous flux or the lumens.

The treatment involving an exposure to a given type of radiation. Often it is in the form of electromagnetic and ionizing radiation such as light (infrared, visible or ultraviolet), x-rays, gamma rays, etc.
The treatment involving growing plants in different types of soil growth media.
The treatment involving an exposure to water with varying degree of temperature, which may depend on regional environment.
The treatment involving an exposure to wind with varying degree of temperature, which may depend on the study type or the regional environment.
The treatment involving continuous exposure of light to the plant.
The treatment involving an exposure of plant to the scheduled or natural exposure of day light and night cycles to the plant.
The treatment involving an exposure to standing water during whole life span of the plant. This also results in anaerobic soil conditions for a long period.
A chemical exposure (PECO:0007189) involving the application of one or more plant growth hormones.

The treatment involving an exposure of plant to the Pythium spinosum. It is a causal agent for rice seedling blight (fungal) or feeder root necrosis or water mold dieases. Water mold diease is also called as seed rot or seedling damping-off disease.
A chemical exposure (PECO:0007189) involving the application of a pesticide; a chemical entity or mixture of chemical entities.
An antibiotic exposure (PECO:0007041) involving use of hygromycin B antibiotic for selection purposes.
The treatment involving exposure of plants to varying levels of pH of the growth media.
The treatment involving an exposure to standing water from flash floods for a small part of plant's life span. This also results in anaerobic soil conditions for a short period.
The treatment involving an exposure to above optimal temperature, which may depend on the study type or the regional environment.
The treatment involving an exposure to cold or sub-optimal temperature, which may depend on the study type or the regional environment.
A physical plant exposure (PECO:0007316) involving an exposure to varying degree of temperature, which may depend on regional environment.
The treatment involving an exposure to a given elevation/height above sea level.
Suggests the exposure of plant to the Pythium myriotylum. It is a causal agent for rice feeder root necrosis disease.

The treatment involving an exposure to a given pressure of the atmosphere at a given point. Its measurement can be expressed in several ways. One is in millibars. Another is in inches or millimeters of mercury (Hg).
The treatment involving exposure of plant to the Pythium irregulare. It is a causal agent for rice feeder root necrosis disease.
An auxin exposure (PECO:0007074) involving use of 2,4-D growth hormone and herbicide.
The treatment involving an exposure to a given amount of rainfall.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to the Pythium graminicola. It is a causal agent for rice feeder root necrosis disease.
A pesticide exposure (PECO:0007167) involving the application of a herbicide; a chemical entity or mixture of chemical entities.

The treatment involving exposure of plant to the Pythium dissotocum. It is a causal agent for rice seedling blight (fungal) or water mold dieases. Water mold diease is also called as seed rot or seedling damping-off disease.
A chemical exposure (PECO:0007189) involving use of salts as supplement to liquid and soil growth media to study various types of responses on their application.

definition.value: This treatment may be used to simulate the growth conditions of sea coast regions and saline/sodic soils.

value.value: The treatment involving exposure of plant to the Pythium catenulatum. It is a causal agent for rice feeder root necrosis disease.
An organic chemical exposure (PECO:0001003) involving the application of salicylic acid (CHEBI:16914).

definition.value: An organic chemical treatment (PECO:0001003) invloving the application of salicylic acid (CHEBI:16914).

value.value: The treatment involving exposure of plant to the Pythium arrhenomanes. It is a causal agent for rice feeder root necrosis disease.
An abiotic plant exposure (PECO:0007191) involving the application of chemical(s).
The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pathogen Ustilaginoidea virens. It is a causal agent for rice False Smut Disease also called as Green Smut disease.
A plant exposure (PECO:0001001) involving the application of chemical or non-biological factors.
The treatment involving exposure of plant to the pathogen Drechslera gigantea. It is a causal agent for rice Eyespot disease.
